JUN 5 2026
THE SENATE
S.B. NO.
THIRTY-THIRD LEGISLATURE, 2026
STATE OF HAWAII
A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO CONSERVATION ENFORCEMENT.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. The legislature finds that the division of
2 conservation and resources enforcement (DOCARE) of the
3 department of land and natural resources will be launching a new
4 academy in 2026 and that a significant number of the incoming
5 conservation and resources enforcement officers will be assigned
6 to the Hawai‘i island branch of DOCARE. The legislature further
7 finds that the Hawai‘i island branch is critically short on
8 vehicles, with the majority of its existing fleet well beyond
9 their intended life of service. The legislature also finds that
10 the upcoming DOCARE academy will include additional marine
11 officers, necessitating an additional maritime patrol vessel for
12 the marine unit based in West Hawai‘i.
13 Accordingly, the purpose of this Act is to appropriate
14 funds for equipment for the Hawai‘i island branch of the division
15 of conservation and resources enforcement of the department of
16 land and natural resources.
2026-2541 SB2756 CDl SMA.docx 1
